WEBVTT

00:00:01.951 --> 00:00:04.888 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now we come to the principal talk

00:00:04.888 --> 00:00:06.923 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of the graduation.

00:00:06.923 --> 00:00:08.792 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s going to be delivered by a member

00:00:08.792 --> 00:00:10.894 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of the Governing Body, 
Brother Stephen Lett.

00:00:10.894 --> 00:00:15.031 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And the very interesting theme 
he has selected is

00:00:15.031 --> 00:00:19.636 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We Can Learn Much From Peter!”

00:00:25.809 --> 00:00:28.545 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Dear Gilead students,

00:00:28.545 --> 00:00:33.550 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
let me ask you,
Who is your favorite Bible character?

00:00:34.751 --> 00:00:36.920 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, during Gilead,

00:00:36.920 --> 00:00:39.823 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you’ve examined many Bible characters;

00:00:39.823 --> 00:00:43.393 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you’ve learned
positive and negative lessons from them.

00:00:43.393 --> 00:00:46.329 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And perhaps your favorite character changed,

00:00:46.329 --> 00:00:48.331 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
remained the same,

00:00:48.331 --> 00:00:52.102 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or now you have 
several favorite Bible characters.

00:00:52.102 --> 00:00:55.872 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But no matter who your favorite character is,

00:00:55.872 --> 00:00:58.908 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
during this talk, we’re going to learn

00:00:58.908 --> 00:01:02.645 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
some of the many lessons to be learned

00:01:02.645 --> 00:01:06.983 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from the very interesting Bible character Peter.

00:01:06.983 --> 00:01:09.986 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now first, let’s learn some things

00:01:09.986 --> 00:01:14.190 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we can learn
about Jehovah and Jesus from Peter.

00:01:14.190 --> 00:01:16.893 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
One thing we definitely learn

00:01:16.893 --> 00:01:21.498 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is that Jehovah and Jesus allow for

00:01:21.498 --> 00:01:23.500 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—in fact, apparently relish—

00:01:23.500 --> 00:01:26.002 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
different personalities among their servants.

00:01:26.002 --> 00:01:28.004 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, to illustrate this,

00:01:28.004 --> 00:01:32.008 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
let’s contrast the personality of Peter

00:01:32.008 --> 00:01:34.978 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with that of some of the other apostles.

00:01:34.978 --> 00:01:37.847 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Open up to John chapter 20,

00:01:37.847 --> 00:01:40.350 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and here’s a very interesting little scripture

00:01:40.350 --> 00:01:43.686 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
highlighting two different personalities.

00:01:43.686 --> 00:01:48.558 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
John 20:3:

00:01:48.558 --> 00:01:53.163 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Then Peter and the other disciple
[who would be John]

00:01:53.163 --> 00:01:55.632 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“set out for the tomb.

00:01:55.632 --> 00:01:58.668 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“The two of them began running together,

00:01:58.668 --> 00:02:03.673 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“but the other disciple ran faster than Peter 
and reached the tomb first.

00:02:03.673 --> 00:02:08.611 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Stooping forward,
he saw the linen cloths lying there,

00:02:08.611 --> 00:02:11.548 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“but he did not go in.

00:02:11.548 --> 00:02:15.718 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Then Simon Peter also came, following him,

00:02:15.718 --> 00:02:20.390 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and he went into the tomb.

00:02:20.390 --> 00:02:23.293 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And he saw the linen cloths lying there.”

00:02:23.293 --> 00:02:28.164 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So John looked inside; Peter rushed inside.

00:02:28.164 --> 00:02:30.700 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, here’s another example:

00:02:30.700 --> 00:02:35.705 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When the mob came
to arrest Jesus in Gethsemane,

00:02:35.705 --> 00:02:38.041 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
John 18:10

00:02:38.041 --> 00:02:41.678 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
says that Peter drew his sword

00:02:41.678 --> 00:02:46.683 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and cut the right ear
of the slave of the high priest off.

00:02:47.517 --> 00:02:49.519 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, let’s think about this.

00:02:49.519 --> 00:02:52.689 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Do you think that Peter
was going for that right ear?

00:02:54.224 --> 00:02:57.160 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I mean, that would truly be impressive
—wouldn’t it?—

00:02:57.160 --> 00:03:01.497 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to go for that right ear and precisely take it off.

00:03:02.398 --> 00:03:06.736 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But remember, Peter was not a swordsman;

00:03:06.736 --> 00:03:09.072 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he was a fisherman.

00:03:09.072 --> 00:03:13.243 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Obviously, he was going
for the man’s head, wasn’t he?

00:03:13.243 --> 00:03:15.445 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But he missed and took the ear off.

00:03:15.445 --> 00:03:18.448 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But what an impetuous,

00:03:18.448 --> 00:03:22.051 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you could say, personality he had there!

00:03:22.051 --> 00:03:24.053 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Here’s one more example:

00:03:24.053 --> 00:03:26.122 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The resurrected Jesus

00:03:26.122 --> 00:03:29.192 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is on the shore of the Sea of Galilee;

00:03:29.192 --> 00:03:32.161 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and the disciples are in the boat;

00:03:32.161 --> 00:03:36.165 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and John says to Peter, “It is the Lord.”

00:03:36.165 --> 00:03:38.735 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, upon hearing this,
Peter put his garment on

00:03:38.735 --> 00:03:40.870 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and plunged into the sea.

00:03:40.870 --> 00:03:43.239 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The other disciples came in the boat.

00:03:43.239 --> 00:03:45.375 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So notice,

00:03:45.375 --> 00:03:48.645 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
John spoke; Peter plunged.

00:03:50.013 --> 00:03:54.183 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The other disciples came in the boat;
Peter came swimming.

00:03:55.251 --> 00:03:57.520 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Very different personalities

00:03:57.520 --> 00:04:00.356 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—but, as we said,
Jehovah and Jesus relish

00:04:00.356 --> 00:04:04.093 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
these different personalities
among their servants.

00:04:04.093 --> 00:04:06.296 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But now, what’s the lesson for us?

00:04:06.296 --> 00:04:09.532 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, in imitation of Jehovah and Jesus,

00:04:09.532 --> 00:04:11.534 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we’re obligated

00:04:11.534 --> 00:04:15.805 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to “have love
for the whole association of [our] brothers.”

00:04:15.805 --> 00:04:17.807 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—1 Peter 2:17.

00:04:17.807 --> 00:04:19.809 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And “whole” means 100 percent.

00:04:19.809 --> 00:04:24.480 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And that certainly includes those
with very different personalities from ourselves

00:04:24.480 --> 00:04:28.217 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—ones from different cultures and backgrounds.

00:04:28.217 --> 00:04:32.422 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We’re obligated to receive these ones

00:04:32.422 --> 00:04:37.427 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
into our company,
into our homes, into our hearts.

00:04:37.427 --> 00:04:40.129 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, you’ve done a lot of this
in the last five months,

00:04:40.129 --> 00:04:42.165 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you Gilead students.

00:04:42.165 --> 00:04:44.167 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, you want to keep doing this

00:04:44.167 --> 00:04:47.603 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and, of course, all of us want to do this.

00:04:47.603 --> 00:04:51.607 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But now, here’s another thing we learn
about Jehovah and Jesus from Peter.

00:04:51.607 --> 00:04:55.545 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah and Jesus are very forgiving.

00:04:55.545 --> 00:04:58.548 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, let’s think about Jesus’ words

00:04:58.548 --> 00:05:01.384 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at Matthew 10:33.

00:05:01.384 --> 00:05:03.653 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In plain words

00:05:03.653 --> 00:05:05.655 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—and our publications have said

00:05:05.655 --> 00:05:09.158 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
probably plain Hebrew words,
it would have been—

00:05:09.158 --> 00:05:11.160 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jesus said:

00:05:11.160 --> 00:05:14.697 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Whoever disowns me before men,

00:05:14.697 --> 00:05:16.933 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I will also disown him

00:05:16.933 --> 00:05:19.869 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
before my Father who is in the heavens.”

00:05:19.869 --> 00:05:24.307 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Not once, not twice,
but three times Peter did it, didn’t he?

00:05:24.307 --> 00:05:27.477 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But yet Jehovah and Jesus
completely forgave him

00:05:27.477 --> 00:05:29.879 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
because he was truly repentant.

00:05:29.879 --> 00:05:33.216 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In fact, to somewhat counterbalance
what Peter had done,

00:05:33.216 --> 00:05:35.318 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jesus allowed Peter

00:05:35.318 --> 00:05:39.222 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to reaffirm his love for Jesus three times.

00:05:39.222 --> 00:05:41.391 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, what’s the lesson for us?

00:05:41.391 --> 00:05:44.227 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We must imitate Jehovah and Jesus

00:05:44.227 --> 00:05:46.229 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in being very forgiving.

00:05:46.229 --> 00:05:50.266 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In fact, Jehovah makes it clear
that He will forgive us

00:05:50.266 --> 00:05:54.303 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in direct proportion to how we forgive others.

00:05:54.303 --> 00:05:57.540 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If we don’t forgive others,
Jehovah won’t forgive us.

00:05:57.540 --> 00:05:59.542 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Where does that leave us?

00:05:59.542 --> 00:06:01.544 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Doomed.

00:06:01.544 --> 00:06:03.913 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But let’s say we do forgive,

00:06:03.913 --> 00:06:06.149 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but we’re pretty tight;
we’re pretty stingy.

00:06:06.149 --> 00:06:09.652 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s kind of hard to squeeze
a little forgiveness out of us.

00:06:09.652 --> 00:06:11.754 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, the indication is that Jehovah puts

00:06:11.754 --> 00:06:15.358 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that same ruler on us that we put on others.

00:06:15.358 --> 00:06:19.162 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
On the other hand,
if we’re very generous in forgiving,

00:06:19.162 --> 00:06:22.465 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
now Jehovah can be 
very generous in forgiving us.

00:06:22.465 --> 00:06:24.634 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So if someone hurt you deeply

00:06:24.634 --> 00:06:26.636 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—has sinned against you—

00:06:26.636 --> 00:06:29.138 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
don’t view this as a bad thing;

00:06:29.138 --> 00:06:32.909 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
view this as a big opportunity.

00:06:32.909 --> 00:06:35.711 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You’ve got a big opportunity

00:06:35.711 --> 00:06:38.448 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to get a lot of forgiveness from Jehovah,

00:06:38.448 --> 00:06:42.118 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
so cash in on that opportunity.

00:06:43.686 --> 00:06:46.189 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But now, in addition to what we can learn

00:06:46.189 --> 00:06:48.224 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
about Jehovah and Jesus from Peter,

00:06:48.224 --> 00:06:51.427 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
there are many lessons (positive and negative)

00:06:51.427 --> 00:06:53.429 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that we can learn from Peter himself.

00:06:53.429 --> 00:06:54.430 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So let’s do that.

00:06:54.430 --> 00:06:56.466 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, here’s a negative lesson:

00:06:56.466 --> 00:07:00.536 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
At times, Peter spoke too quickly.

00:07:00.536 --> 00:07:05.541 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He had what has been called
hoof-and-mouth disease.

00:07:06.209 --> 00:07:07.543 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What is that?

00:07:07.543 --> 00:07:09.545 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Open mouth; insert foot.

00:07:09.545 --> 00:07:13.049 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And some of us
have the same problem, don’t we?

00:07:13.049 --> 00:07:16.085 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But here’s an example in Matthew chapter 16.

00:07:16.085 --> 00:07:20.289 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jesus was explaining
that he would have to go to Jerusalem,

00:07:20.289 --> 00:07:23.493 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
suffer many things, and be killed.

00:07:23.493 --> 00:07:25.928 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, quickly Peter spoke up,

00:07:25.928 --> 00:07:27.964 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and he actually rebuked Jesus

00:07:27.964 --> 00:07:30.032 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—if you can imagine that.

00:07:30.032 --> 00:07:33.236 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Be kind to yourself, Lord;

00:07:33.236 --> 00:07:36.973 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you will not have this happen to you at all.”

00:07:36.973 --> 00:07:39.775 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was hoof-and-mouth disease
—wasn’t it?—

00:07:39.775 --> 00:07:42.445 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
followed by, as you could expect,

00:07:42.445 --> 00:07:45.414 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
some correction, humiliation:

00:07:45.414 --> 00:07:48.885 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Get behind me, Satan!”

00:07:48.885 --> 00:07:51.020 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But the indication is

00:07:51.020 --> 00:07:55.091 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that even though Peter
had this problem, he overcame it.

00:07:55.091 --> 00:07:57.093 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He overcame this.

00:07:57.093 --> 00:07:59.562 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Several times he spoke too quickly.

00:07:59.562 --> 00:08:02.265 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But at 1 Peter 3:10,

00:08:02.265 --> 00:08:05.301 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he was able to write 
with freeness of speech,

00:08:05.301 --> 00:08:07.637 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we know,
and he would have lived up to this:

00:08:07.637 --> 00:08:12.475 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Whoever would love life and see good days

00:08:12.475 --> 00:08:14.977 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
must guard his tongue.”

00:08:14.977 --> 00:08:16.245 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So he learned.

00:08:16.245 --> 00:08:17.246 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It took time.

00:08:17.246 --> 00:08:20.183 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He learned just like we’re all learning.

00:08:20.183 --> 00:08:22.118 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But now, what’s the lesson for us?

00:08:22.118 --> 00:08:25.621 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, it’s summed up nicely here
in Proverbs chapter 18.

00:08:25.621 --> 00:08:26.689 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Please go there.

00:08:26.689 --> 00:08:29.458 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Proverbs 18:13:

00:08:29.458 --> 00:08:34.297 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“When anyone replies
to a matter before he hears the facts,

00:08:34.297 --> 00:08:38.067 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
it is foolish and humiliating.”

00:08:38.067 --> 00:08:42.672 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So none of us can perfectly bridle our tongues.

00:08:42.672 --> 00:08:46.209 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But we do well to try to restrain our lips,

00:08:46.209 --> 00:08:49.712 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at least until we’ve heard the facts.

00:08:49.712 --> 00:08:52.081 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, here’s another negative lesson:

00:08:52.081 --> 00:08:55.952 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
At times, Peter was overconfident.

00:08:55.952 --> 00:08:58.454 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The most notorious example

00:08:58.454 --> 00:09:00.823 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—Matthew chapter 26:

00:09:00.823 --> 00:09:05.561 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Although all the others
are stumbled in connection with you,

00:09:05.561 --> 00:09:08.464 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I will never be stumbled!

00:09:08.464 --> 00:09:11.300 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Even if I should have to die with you,

00:09:11.300 --> 00:09:14.470 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I will by no means disown you.”

00:09:14.470 --> 00:09:16.839 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, that was overconfidence, wasn’t it?

00:09:16.839 --> 00:09:20.142 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And we know it was ‘pride before the crash.’

00:09:20.142 --> 00:09:22.311 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, what was his problem?

00:09:22.311 --> 00:09:26.249 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He was relying,
at this point, on himself

00:09:26.249 --> 00:09:28.284 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
rather than Jehovah.

00:09:28.284 --> 00:09:30.786 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But again, the indication is very strong

00:09:30.786 --> 00:09:33.222 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that he overcame that weakness.

00:09:33.222 --> 00:09:36.392 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And later, he was able to write at 1 Peter 5:6:

00:09:36.392 --> 00:09:41.397 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Humble yourselves, therefore,
under the mighty hand of God.”

00:09:41.397 --> 00:09:43.799 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So don’t rely on yourself.

00:09:43.799 --> 00:09:46.902 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Be humble under Jehovah’s hand.

00:09:46.902 --> 00:09:48.904 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, what’s the lesson for us?

00:09:48.904 --> 00:09:50.906 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, like we learned at our convention

00:09:50.906 --> 00:09:53.476 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—the last talk on Saturday—

00:09:53.476 --> 00:09:57.747 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that true courage is not self-reliance.

00:09:57.747 --> 00:10:01.350 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
True courage must be based

00:10:01.350 --> 00:10:05.021 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
on modest reliance on Jehovah.

00:10:05.021 --> 00:10:08.891 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When we lean on ourselves,
or rely on ourselves,

00:10:08.891 --> 00:10:13.729 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
it’s like leaning,
you could say, on a rubber crutch.

00:10:13.729 --> 00:10:16.232 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Did you ever lean on a rubber crutch?

00:10:16.232 --> 00:10:18.334 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You’re going to fall, aren’t you?

00:10:18.334 --> 00:10:22.905 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But at Deuteronomy 32:4,
Jehovah is “the Rock.”

00:10:22.905 --> 00:10:25.741 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If you lean on a rock,
now you have something.

00:10:25.741 --> 00:10:28.678 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So we learn that from Peter:

00:10:28.678 --> 00:10:32.181 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Don’t rely on yourself;
rely always on Jehovah.

00:10:32.181 --> 00:10:34.383 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, here’s one more negative lesson:

00:10:34.383 --> 00:10:37.153 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
At times, Peter was ensnared

00:10:37.153 --> 00:10:39.155 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
by fear of man

00:10:39.155 --> 00:10:42.491 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or, we could say, 
in his most infamous example,

00:10:42.491 --> 00:10:44.493 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
fear of girl.

00:10:47.096 --> 00:10:50.533 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Interestingly, in Matthew 26:

00:10:50.533 --> 00:10:55.538 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Peter was sitting outside
and a servant girl came up and said to him:

00:10:55.538 --> 00:10:59.175 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘“You too were with Jesus the Galilean!”

00:10:59.175 --> 00:11:01.077 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘But he denied it.

00:11:01.077 --> 00:11:04.280 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘“I do not know what you’re talking about.”

00:11:04.280 --> 00:11:08.751 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘He went out to the gatehouse;
another girl noticed him.

00:11:08.751 --> 00:11:11.587 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘“This man was with Jesus.”

00:11:11.587 --> 00:11:15.891 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Again he denied it, even with an oath.’

00:11:15.891 --> 00:11:20.496 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So his first two denials,
you could say, were fear of girl.

00:11:22.398 --> 00:11:26.068 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But it is obviously clear

00:11:26.068 --> 00:11:30.606 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that he truly overcame
that weakness, that problem,

00:11:30.606 --> 00:11:32.608 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and he became

00:11:32.608 --> 00:11:36.946 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
an outspoken, bold Witness
of Jehovah and Jesus.

00:11:36.946 --> 00:11:40.383 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Think, for example, in Acts chapter 5,

00:11:40.383 --> 00:11:45.087 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
where Peter and the other apostles
were in front of the Sanhedrin,

00:11:45.087 --> 00:11:48.157 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and the high priest said:
‘We ordered you

00:11:48.157 --> 00:11:51.160 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to quit teaching about this Jesus.’

00:11:51.160 --> 00:11:56.165 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Peter said:
“We must obey God as ruler rather than men.”

00:11:57.299 --> 00:12:02.304 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘And furthermore, this Jesus,
God has raised him from the dead.

00:12:02.304 --> 00:12:06.575 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This one that you killed.’

00:12:06.575 --> 00:12:08.677 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Wow!

00:12:08.677 --> 00:12:11.380 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
No fear of man there, was there?

00:12:11.380 --> 00:12:14.283 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He obviously overcame this problem.

00:12:14.283 --> 00:12:16.285 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, what’s the lesson for us?

00:12:16.285 --> 00:12:20.523 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We want to do our utmost to never be ensnared

00:12:20.523 --> 00:12:24.026 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
by fear of men, women, or girls.

00:12:26.629 --> 00:12:28.798 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And, of course, always remembering

00:12:28.798 --> 00:12:32.134 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that it’s Jehovah’s rating of us
that counts will help us.

00:12:32.134 --> 00:12:35.471 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Humans can’t add five seconds
to their life, can they?

00:12:35.471 --> 00:12:39.341 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah can add or subtract eternity.

00:12:39.341 --> 00:12:41.343 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But now, we’re going to move

00:12:41.343 --> 00:12:44.013 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to some positive lessons
we can learn from Peter.

00:12:44.013 --> 00:12:46.982 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And by far, his positive qualities

00:12:46.982 --> 00:12:51.554 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
outweigh the negative qualities
that he displayed at times.

00:12:51.554 --> 00:12:56.559 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now here’s one:
Peter waited on Jehovah.

00:12:57.193 --> 00:13:01.564 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And a wonderful example
of this is in John chapter 6.

00:13:01.564 --> 00:13:05.501 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jesus had stated
that unless you eat my flesh

00:13:05.501 --> 00:13:07.536 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and drink my blood,

00:13:07.536 --> 00:13:10.039 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you will not have everlasting life.

00:13:10.039 --> 00:13:14.076 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And the Bible says
that many of the disciples were shocked;

00:13:14.076 --> 00:13:16.912 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
they were stumbled;
they quit following Jesus.

00:13:16.912 --> 00:13:21.484 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And Jesus said to Peter,
‘Do you want to leave also, Peter?’

00:13:21.484 --> 00:13:25.187 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Do you remember those beautiful words
coming out of Peter’s mouth?

00:13:25.187 --> 00:13:29.725 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Lord, whom shall we go away to?

00:13:29.725 --> 00:13:33.095 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You have [the] sayings of everlasting life.”

00:13:33.095 --> 00:13:36.765 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, if you think about it,
Peter didn’t understand Jesus’ words

00:13:36.765 --> 00:13:39.468 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at this point any more than the rest did,

00:13:39.468 --> 00:13:43.906 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but he was willing to wait
on Jehovah for further enlightenment.

00:13:43.906 --> 00:13:47.142 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And in time, he learned that those words

00:13:47.142 --> 00:13:49.178 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
have to be understood figuratively

00:13:49.178 --> 00:13:51.780 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—that we have to exercise faith

00:13:51.780 --> 00:13:54.416 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in Jesus’ flesh and blood.

00:13:54.416 --> 00:13:56.418 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, what’s the lesson for us?

00:13:56.418 --> 00:13:59.021 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Like Peter, we must show

00:13:59.021 --> 00:14:03.759 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a waiting attitude
for the “God of [our] salvation.”

00:14:03.759 --> 00:14:05.861 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—Micah 7:7.

00:14:05.861 --> 00:14:07.897 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, here are just a few examples:

00:14:07.897 --> 00:14:11.400 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Are we willing to wait
—and this was touched on earlier in our program—

00:14:11.400 --> 00:14:14.336 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
willing to wait with the right attitude

00:14:14.336 --> 00:14:17.873 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for any theocratic appointment,

00:14:17.873 --> 00:14:20.242 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or privilege of service?

00:14:20.242 --> 00:14:22.244 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Here’s another example:

00:14:22.244 --> 00:14:27.082 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Are we willing to wait uncomplainingly
on Jehovah to correct

00:14:27.082 --> 00:14:29.518 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—in his way, his time—

00:14:29.518 --> 00:14:34.523 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
any injustice that we perceive
in the congregation?

00:14:34.523 --> 00:14:36.025 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Or what about this?

00:14:36.025 --> 00:14:38.460 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Are we willing to wait patiently

00:14:38.460 --> 00:14:40.896 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—and this could apply   
to some of the single ones—

00:14:40.896 --> 00:14:43.799 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Are you willing to wait patiently on Jehovah

00:14:43.799 --> 00:14:47.403 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to provide you a suitable marriage mate,

00:14:47.403 --> 00:14:50.906 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
even if you have to wait until the new world?

00:14:50.906 --> 00:14:55.511 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes, like Peter, let’s have a waiting attitude.

00:14:55.511 --> 00:14:58.247 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But now,
here’s another positive lesson from Peter:

00:14:58.247 --> 00:15:01.250 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In order to make progress spiritually,

00:15:01.250 --> 00:15:06.021 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he was willing to move out of his comfort zones.

00:15:06.021 --> 00:15:08.123 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, let’s get some examples.

00:15:08.123 --> 00:15:13.128 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When invited, he promptly left
a life of pursuing material things

00:15:13.128 --> 00:15:17.232 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for a life of storing up treasure in heaven.

00:15:17.232 --> 00:15:21.670 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And apparently,
he was an older man when he did this.

00:15:21.670 --> 00:15:26.575 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But he did not put
financial security ahead of following the Christ.

00:15:26.575 --> 00:15:28.410 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Or here’s another example:

00:15:28.410 --> 00:15:31.714 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He went from being
an unlettered, ordinary fisherman,

00:15:31.714 --> 00:15:36.051 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
probably talking primarily
to hired men and fish merchants,

00:15:36.051 --> 00:15:39.622 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to being a bold Witness

00:15:39.622 --> 00:15:44.627 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of an unpopular message before thousands.

00:15:44.627 --> 00:15:46.128 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
One more example:

00:15:46.128 --> 00:15:48.797 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He went from being very prejudiced

00:15:48.797 --> 00:15:52.901 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
against Samaritans and Gentiles

00:15:52.901 --> 00:15:57.906 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to truly loving
his Samaritan and Gentile brothers.

00:15:58.474 --> 00:16:00.209 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, what’s the lesson for us?

00:16:00.209 --> 00:16:03.078 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Are we willing to move out of our comfort zones

00:16:03.078 --> 00:16:05.080 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in order to make spiritual progress?

00:16:05.080 --> 00:16:08.984 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, all of you,
you know where your comfort zones are.

00:16:08.984 --> 00:16:13.689 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But are you willing to move out
in order to make spiritual progress?

00:16:13.689 --> 00:16:18.227 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What about, in some cases,
especially if you’re given an assignment,

00:16:18.227 --> 00:16:20.596 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
are you willing to go
where the need is greater,

00:16:20.596 --> 00:16:23.032 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
where Jehovah wants you to go?

00:16:23.032 --> 00:16:26.268 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Or what about reaching out
for various forms of the ministry

00:16:26.268 --> 00:16:29.271 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that you may not right now feel
so comfortable with

00:16:29.271 --> 00:16:33.208 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—maybe public witnessing
or working business territory?

00:16:33.208 --> 00:16:38.213 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What about being
more courageous in informal witnessing,

00:16:38.213 --> 00:16:42.785 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
even though you may be
a quiet and shy type of person?

00:16:43.752 --> 00:16:46.755 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, let’s get
another positive lesson from Peter.

00:16:46.755 --> 00:16:49.091 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He allowed discipline

00:16:49.091 --> 00:16:53.495 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to mold rather than stumble him.

00:16:54.563 --> 00:16:59.068 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Of all the apostles,
he was the most outspoken, wasn’t he?

00:16:59.068 --> 00:17:03.505 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But that was matched
by his being the most frequently corrected,

00:17:03.505 --> 00:17:06.341 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
reproved, rebuked.

00:17:06.341 --> 00:17:10.245 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But beautifully, he didn’t quit.

00:17:10.245 --> 00:17:12.247 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He never gave up, did he?

00:17:12.247 --> 00:17:16.218 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
For example, we touched on this before,
when Jesus said, “Get behind me, Satan!”

00:17:16.218 --> 00:17:19.788 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We don’t read
that he pouted for weeks or months

00:17:19.788 --> 00:17:22.391 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
because of that strong correction.

00:17:22.391 --> 00:17:25.561 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In fact, the Bible indicates that six days later,

00:17:25.561 --> 00:17:28.897 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jesus took Peter, James, and John

00:17:28.897 --> 00:17:31.967 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
up into a mountain
to experience the transfiguration.

00:17:31.967 --> 00:17:35.571 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Or what about after Peter denied Jesus?

00:17:35.571 --> 00:17:39.508 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Bible tells us 
that Jesus looked straight at Peter

00:17:39.508 --> 00:17:42.578 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—in effect, indirect discipline.

00:17:42.578 --> 00:17:45.080 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Peter recalled what Jesus said.

00:17:45.080 --> 00:17:48.617 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He went outside, and he wept bitterly.

00:17:48.617 --> 00:17:52.321 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But yet you don’t read
that he kept beating himself

00:17:52.321 --> 00:17:57.326 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—he kept being depressed
over his serious sin of denying Jesus.

00:17:57.326 --> 00:18:00.329 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He knew Jehovah and Jesus had forgiven him.

00:18:00.329 --> 00:18:02.498 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So he put it behind him
—didn’t he?—

00:18:02.498 --> 00:18:04.500 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and he moved ahead.

00:18:04.500 --> 00:18:06.535 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, the lesson for us?

00:18:06.535 --> 00:18:09.738 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah disciplines those he loves.

00:18:09.738 --> 00:18:13.342 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But don’t ever let 
that discipline harden or embitter you.

00:18:13.342 --> 00:18:17.813 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let it soften you into a better person.

00:18:17.813 --> 00:18:20.082 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If we’ve committed sins in the past,

00:18:20.082 --> 00:18:22.851 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
even serious sins, like Peter,

00:18:22.851 --> 00:18:26.922 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
let’s put them behind us and move ahead.

00:18:26.922 --> 00:18:31.393 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, one more positive lesson
we’re going to talk about from Peter:

00:18:31.393 --> 00:18:35.764 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He gained and then he maintained

00:18:35.764 --> 00:18:37.833 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
true humility.

00:18:37.833 --> 00:18:41.303 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, it’s true that he 
had to really work hard to gain it, didn’t he?

00:18:41.303 --> 00:18:44.606 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He had to work at it
because he and the other apostles

00:18:44.606 --> 00:18:46.608 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
had been taught from infancy

00:18:46.608 --> 00:18:50.078 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to strive to be the greatest
—seek prominence.

00:18:50.078 --> 00:18:53.882 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was really indoctrinated
into their minds and hearts.

00:18:53.882 --> 00:18:58.287 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And up until the very last night
of Jesus’ life on the earth,

00:18:58.287 --> 00:19:00.289 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Peter still had a problem
—didn’t he?—

00:19:00.289 --> 00:19:01.890 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and the other apostles too.

00:19:01.890 --> 00:19:03.392 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He had a problem.

00:19:03.392 --> 00:19:06.061 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jesus was washing the feet.

00:19:06.061 --> 00:19:11.066 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
John chapter 13
—Peter had not volunteered to do this

00:19:11.066 --> 00:19:14.570 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
even after Jesus started washing the feet.

00:19:14.570 --> 00:19:16.171 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Have you ever thought about that?

00:19:16.171 --> 00:19:19.975 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Sometimes you don’t think of something
until someone else starts doing it,

00:19:19.975 --> 00:19:22.311 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and you think,
‘Oh, well, let me help you with that.’

00:19:22.311 --> 00:19:24.746 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Did Peter say: ‘Oh. Oh, Lord.

00:19:24.746 --> 00:19:26.748 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘I see you’re washing these feet here.

00:19:26.748 --> 00:19:30.319 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let me help you.
Let me catch a couple of feet for you.’

00:19:31.854 --> 00:19:36.558 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
No. 
Neither he nor any of the apostles volunteered.

00:19:36.558 --> 00:19:39.027 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They still had a problem at this point.

00:19:39.027 --> 00:19:43.532 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But with Jehovah’s help and effort on his part,

00:19:43.532 --> 00:19:47.536 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in time, he truly developed true humility.

00:19:47.536 --> 00:19:50.606 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He went from the one striving to be the greatest

00:19:50.606 --> 00:19:54.910 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to the humbled man who lifted up Cornelius

00:19:54.910 --> 00:19:57.646 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when Cornelius tried to bow down to him.

00:19:57.646 --> 00:20:00.682 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Remember that account in Acts chapter 10?

00:20:00.682 --> 00:20:03.018 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Peter lifted him up, saying:

00:20:03.018 --> 00:20:07.923 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Rise; I too am just a man.’”

00:20:08.557 --> 00:20:10.993 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Or what about his genuine humility

00:20:10.993 --> 00:20:14.196 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when the apostle Paul corrected him publicly

00:20:14.196 --> 00:20:16.198 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in front of the whole congregation?

00:20:16.198 --> 00:20:18.333 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, if he would have still had pride—

00:20:18.333 --> 00:20:22.471 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Well, who are you, Paul, to give me correction?

00:20:22.471 --> 00:20:25.240 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘I’ve been in the truth a lot longer than you have.

00:20:25.240 --> 00:20:27.442 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘When you were persecuting the Christians,

00:20:27.442 --> 00:20:29.544 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘I was an apostle.

00:20:29.544 --> 00:20:33.148 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘And furthermore,
you could have at least talked to me privately,

00:20:33.148 --> 00:20:35.984 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
not in front of the whole congregation.’

00:20:35.984 --> 00:20:39.755 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But no, he knew he was clearly wrong.

00:20:39.755 --> 00:20:42.591 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He deserved the counsel
no matter how it was given.

00:20:42.591 --> 00:20:44.593 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He made the correction,

00:20:44.593 --> 00:20:48.096 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and he harbored no grudge.

00:20:48.096 --> 00:20:50.899 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And the indication is very powerful

00:20:50.899 --> 00:20:53.101 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that he remained humble

00:20:53.101 --> 00:20:55.704 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
despite his many privileges.

00:20:55.704 --> 00:21:00.142 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I mean, looking back over his life,
he had had many, many privileges.

00:21:00.142 --> 00:21:01.843 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Isn’t that true?

00:21:01.843 --> 00:21:05.380 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He walked on water, at least for a few minutes;

00:21:06.782 --> 00:21:09.885 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he saw Jesus transfigured;

00:21:09.885 --> 00:21:14.756 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he performed many miracles,
including personally resurrecting Dorcas;

00:21:14.756 --> 00:21:18.493 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he received and used “the keys of the Kingdom”;

00:21:18.493 --> 00:21:20.929 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he helped many people into the truth.

00:21:20.929 --> 00:21:23.865 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But yet he remained truly humble

00:21:23.865 --> 00:21:26.468 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and could write with freeness of speech

00:21:26.468 --> 00:21:28.704 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in his inspired letter,

00:21:28.704 --> 00:21:31.707 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at 1 Peter 5:5,

00:21:31.707 --> 00:21:35.043 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
these beautiful words that we read very often.

00:21:35.043 --> 00:21:40.048 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He said:
“But all of you clothe yourselves

00:21:40.048 --> 00:21:43.518 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“with humility toward one another,

00:21:43.518 --> 00:21:47.155 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“because God opposes the haughty ones,

00:21:47.155 --> 00:21:51.660 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but he gives
undeserved kindness to the humble ones.”

00:21:51.660 --> 00:21:54.129 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And where is Peter right now?

00:21:54.129 --> 00:21:56.865 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
An immortal spirit

00:21:56.865 --> 00:22:00.869 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
serving as one of the “12 foundation stones”

00:22:00.869 --> 00:22:03.205 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of the Messianic Kingdom.

00:22:03.205 --> 00:22:06.208 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So, what is the lesson for us?

00:22:06.208 --> 00:22:10.645 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We must gain true humility like Peter did.

00:22:10.645 --> 00:22:15.317 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Otherwise, if you think about it,
we’re absolutely unusable by Jehovah.

00:22:15.317 --> 00:22:18.653 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And then, we must remain humble

00:22:18.653 --> 00:22:23.225 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
no matter what privileges
we may or may not receive,

00:22:23.225 --> 00:22:27.396 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and then Jehovah will never oppose us.

00:22:27.396 --> 00:22:32.434 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Rather, we will continue to receive
undeserved kindness from him.

00:22:33.235 --> 00:22:36.171 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, our discussion has highlighted

00:22:36.171 --> 00:22:41.176 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
