to be learned from Peter.

00:22:41.176 --> 00:22:44.880 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’m sure that if you Gilead students
—soon-to-be graduates—

00:22:44.880 --> 00:22:47.783 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
make Peter a study project,

00:22:47.783 --> 00:22:51.920 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you could learn
many, many more valuable lessons

00:22:51.920 --> 00:22:55.624 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and, of course,
that’s true of many other Bible characters.

00:22:55.624 --> 00:22:59.895 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But unquestionably,
there is so much to learn

00:22:59.895 --> 00:23:05.934 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from the faithful, colorful, human apostle Peter.

