00:29:41.162 --> 00:29:43.665 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“September 8, 2018.

00:29:43.665 --> 00:29:47.469 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“To the Governing Body 
and the Bethel Family.

00:29:47.469 --> 00:29:50.605 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Dear Brothers: Five months ago,

00:29:50.605 --> 00:29:54.409 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“we arrived with excitement 
from the four corners of the earth.

00:29:54.409 --> 00:29:57.512 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We anxiously waited 
to be molded into the people

00:29:57.512 --> 00:30:00.882 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“that our Father, Jehovah, 
knew we could become.

00:30:00.882 --> 00:30:05.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Despite denied visas, 
health issues, and insecurities,

00:30:05.854 --> 00:30:09.190 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“we were prepared 
to be taught by our Grand Instructor.

00:30:09.190 --> 00:30:13.995 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Even after enrollment, 
further challenges presented themselves.

00:30:13.995 --> 00:30:17.365 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“As a class, we fought measles,

00:30:17.365 --> 00:30:21.936 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“endured quarantine, survived tornadoes,

00:30:21.936 --> 00:30:24.272 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“nursed broken bones,

00:30:24.272 --> 00:30:27.575 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and comforted each other 
in the face of bereavement.

00:30:27.575 --> 00:30:31.379 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“However, these hurdles 
did not hamper us;

00:30:31.379 --> 00:30:34.182 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“they drew us closer together as siblings

00:30:34.182 --> 00:30:36.351 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and to our Father, Jehovah.

00:30:36.351 --> 00:30:39.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Isaiah gave us a glimpse 
into a heavenly school

00:30:39.854 --> 00:30:43.525 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“when he described the training Jesus 
was then receiving from Jehovah

00:30:43.525 --> 00:30:46.261 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to prepare him for his earthly assignment.

00:30:46.261 --> 00:30:50.965 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Isaiah 50:4 describes 
Jesus’ special education saying:

00:30:50.965 --> 00:30:53.801 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘He awakens me morning by morning;

00:30:53.801 --> 00:30:58.273 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘he awakens my ear 
to listen like the taught ones.’

00:30:58.273 --> 00:31:01.976 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Jesus knew very well 
the purpose of his training:

00:31:01.976 --> 00:31:06.981 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘So that [he] may know how to answer 
the tired one with the right word.’

00:31:06.981 --> 00:31:09.617 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Out of deep love and appreciation,

00:31:09.617 --> 00:31:12.921 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“he became 
the perfect reflection of his Father.

00:31:12.921 --> 00:31:16.324 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We too know very well 
the purpose of the loving training

00:31:16.324 --> 00:31:18.426 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“we have received here at Gilead

00:31:18.426 --> 00:31:22.263 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“—to answer the tired one, 
not out of our own thoughts,

00:31:22.263 --> 00:31:26.100 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“but with the words 
taught to us through God’s Word.

00:31:26.100 --> 00:31:29.337 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Many in the brotherhood 
are like a smoldering wick

00:31:29.337 --> 00:31:31.573 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and at times feel crushed in spirit.

00:31:31.573 --> 00:31:34.208 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Jesus loved and cared for such ones.

00:31:34.208 --> 00:31:37.545 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“We are determined 
to reflect the love Jesus developed

00:31:37.545 --> 00:31:40.181 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“through his schooling and bring true comfort

00:31:40.181 --> 00:31:42.984 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and refreshment to our brothers.

00:31:42.984 --> 00:31:45.820 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Words fail to express the depth of our gratitude

00:31:45.820 --> 00:31:48.056 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“for all that has been done for us.

00:31:48.056 --> 00:31:50.525 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“The Bethel family 
welcomed us into their home

00:31:50.525 --> 00:31:54.128 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and showed hospitality 
to a degree that we never imagined.

00:31:54.128 --> 00:31:57.131 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Our dear instructors became like fathers,

00:31:57.131 --> 00:31:59.300 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“teaching us with grace and dignity.

00:31:59.300 --> 00:32:03.871 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“They showed us how to honor 
one another through their example.

00:32:03.871 --> 00:32:06.908 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“They took the time 
to comfort us in the face of trials.

00:32:06.908 --> 00:32:10.011 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“The winsome words 
we received through the curriculum

00:32:10.011 --> 00:32:12.580 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“were as soothing oil on our souls,

00:32:12.580 --> 00:32:15.383 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“healing and strengthening us 
for the days ahead.

00:32:15.383 --> 00:32:19.320 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“For this,
we wish to deeply thank our instructors

00:32:19.320 --> 00:32:22.690 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“as well as you dear brothers
on the Governing Body.

00:32:22.690 --> 00:32:26.961 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“It is now clearer than ever to us
that Jehovah is using you mightily

00:32:26.961 --> 00:32:30.465 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“in fulfilling your weighty assignment
of overseeing the preaching work.

00:32:30.465 --> 00:32:33.034 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Above all, we must thank

00:32:33.034 --> 00:32:35.370 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“our Father, Jehovah,
from the bottom of our hearts

00:32:35.370 --> 00:32:38.006 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“for this precious and unforgettable gift.

00:32:38.006 --> 00:32:40.508 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Jehovah truly has given us

00:32:40.508 --> 00:32:45.413 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“‘more than superabundantly 
beyond all the things we ask.’

00:32:45.413 --> 00:32:48.583 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“At the end of this life-defining experience,

00:32:48.583 --> 00:32:52.020 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“we know our molding is far from complete.

00:32:52.020 --> 00:32:54.722 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Our learning will continue.

00:32:54.722 --> 00:32:58.393 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Our gratitude compels us to do our utmost

00:32:58.393 --> 00:33:01.229 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to support you in all that we do.

00:33:01.229 --> 00:33:05.266 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Our hearts overflow with excitement
to work harder than ever before.

00:33:05.266 --> 00:33:10.004 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“May Jehovah continue to richly bless
the marvelous provision of Gilead

00:33:10.004 --> 00:33:12.473 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“to the benefit of the worldwide brotherhood

00:33:12.473 --> 00:33:16.310 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and the praise and honor
of our most wonderful God, Jehovah.

00:33:16.310 --> 00:33:20.214 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Your brothers and sisters,
the 145th Class of Gilead.”

00:33:26.921 --> 00:33:28.956 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, this is my opportunity

00:33:28.956 --> 00:33:31.926 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to say just a few final words to you.

00:33:31.926 --> 00:33:34.128 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There have been so many wonderful points

00:33:34.128 --> 00:33:36.431 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
mentioned on our program today.

00:33:36.431 --> 00:33:39.133 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Remember how
we started with our discussion

00:33:39.133 --> 00:33:43.137 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
about the need
to always bring glory to Jehovah

00:33:43.137 --> 00:33:45.440 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and not to be concerned
about our own glory.

00:33:45.440 --> 00:33:48.176 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You remember
we started off by mentioning

00:33:48.176 --> 00:33:50.578 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that maybe it could be tempting

00:33:50.578 --> 00:33:53.448 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to accept glory
from others if they praise us.

00:33:53.448 --> 00:33:56.384 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But then on the other hand,
if we get criticized,

00:33:56.384 --> 00:34:00.488 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
it may also be tempting
for us to try and justify ourselves

00:34:00.488 --> 00:34:04.325 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and inadvertently bring glory to ourselves.

00:34:04.325 --> 00:34:08.329 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But there is another way too
that we may have to be careful

00:34:08.329 --> 00:34:11.265 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
about not bringing glory to ourselves.

00:34:11.265 --> 00:34:13.301 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And we can see this

00:34:13.301 --> 00:34:15.837 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from the example of the apostle Paul.

00:34:15.837 --> 00:34:17.705 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, I know you didn’t bring your Bibles up.

00:34:17.705 --> 00:34:19.607 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All you have to do is listen.

00:34:19.607 --> 00:34:23.611 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s one scripture, 1 Corinthians chapter 2

00:34:23.611 --> 00:34:26.247 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—1 Corinthians 2:1, 2.

00:34:26.247 --> 00:34:29.917 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s a vital lesson
that we learn from the apostle Paul.

00:34:29.917 --> 00:34:33.554 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Here he’s speaking
about when he went to Corinth.

00:34:33.554 --> 00:34:36.958 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And as we realize,
Corinth was a seat of learning.

00:34:36.958 --> 00:34:38.726 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Greeks loved learning.

00:34:38.726 --> 00:34:40.394 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And what did he say?

00:34:40.394 --> 00:34:42.163 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In verses 1 and 2:

00:34:42.163 --> 00:34:44.799 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“So when I came to you, brothers,

00:34:44.799 --> 00:34:48.803 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I did not come with extravagant speech

00:34:48.803 --> 00:34:52.874 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or wisdom declaring 
the sacred secret of God to you.”

00:34:52.874 --> 00:34:54.876 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So Paul didn’t use

00:34:54.876 --> 00:34:58.279 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“extravagant speech” to impress people.

00:34:58.279 --> 00:35:01.749 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He says in verse 2: “For I decided.”

00:35:01.749 --> 00:35:03.751 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes, he made a decision.

00:35:03.751 --> 00:35:04.952 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What was it?

00:35:04.952 --> 00:35:07.421 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I decided not to know anything

00:35:07.421 --> 00:35:10.224 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
among you except Jesus Christ.”

00:35:10.224 --> 00:35:12.894 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And then if we look at verse 5,

00:35:12.894 --> 00:35:15.797 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he says: “So that your faith [may] be,

00:35:15.797 --> 00:35:19.634 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
not in men’s wisdom, but in God’s power.”

00:35:19.634 --> 00:35:22.303 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What a wonderful example Paul set

00:35:22.303 --> 00:35:24.772 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with regard to not drawing attention

00:35:24.772 --> 00:35:27.642 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to his own wisdom and ability,

00:35:27.642 --> 00:35:30.478 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
even though some
in Corinth because of this

00:35:30.478 --> 00:35:33.114 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
felt he wasn’t a very good speaker.

00:35:33.114 --> 00:35:36.717 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When we look at how
Paul defended the good news

00:35:36.717 --> 00:35:39.287 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
before audiences large and small,

00:35:39.287 --> 00:35:43.291 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he certainly was a very, very good orator.

00:35:43.291 --> 00:35:46.127 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He had that ability, but he decided

00:35:46.127 --> 00:35:48.596 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to tone it down

00:35:48.596 --> 00:35:51.732 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
because he knew
the brothers there had a weakness.

00:35:51.732 --> 00:35:55.136 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, what weaknesses
were prevalent at that time?

00:35:55.136 --> 00:35:57.305 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, among the Jewish people

00:35:57.305 --> 00:36:00.374 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—and there were some Jewish people
there in Corinth as well—

00:36:00.374 --> 00:36:04.478 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
they loved to quote great rabbis

00:36:04.478 --> 00:36:06.848 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and scholars.

00:36:06.848 --> 00:36:11.519 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And, of course, the Greeks loved
to quote the philosophers.

00:36:11.519 --> 00:36:15.122 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So, what lesson
do you think we learn from this?

00:36:15.122 --> 00:36:17.992 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, now as you go to your assignments,

00:36:17.992 --> 00:36:21.128 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
perhaps you might be tempted to say:

00:36:21.128 --> 00:36:24.365 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Oh! The instructor

00:36:24.365 --> 00:36:28.436 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or a Governing Body member said this.”

00:36:30.171 --> 00:36:32.306 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But why should we follow

00:36:32.306 --> 00:36:34.475 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the example of the apostle Paul?

00:36:34.475 --> 00:36:37.678 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, you see,
if we have something worthwhile

00:36:37.678 --> 00:36:39.947 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to convey to the brothers and sisters,

00:36:39.947 --> 00:36:42.950 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
find it in God’s Word
as you’ve been searching.

00:36:42.950 --> 00:36:45.419 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Look in the library—Watchtower Library.

00:36:45.419 --> 00:36:48.122 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Find something there, but don’t rely

00:36:48.122 --> 00:36:51.259 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
upon the “rabbis,”

00:36:51.259 --> 00:36:54.061 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the “gurus,”

00:36:54.061 --> 00:36:57.398 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to show that you have
some inside knowledge

00:36:57.398 --> 00:37:01.535 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that cannot be verified
by other mere mortals.

00:37:01.535 --> 00:37:05.339 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Rather, rely upon God’s Word.

00:37:05.339 --> 00:37:08.309 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes, rely on his Word and the publications

00:37:08.309 --> 00:37:10.378 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that we have through his organization,

00:37:10.378 --> 00:37:12.580 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and in that way, you can be sure

00:37:12.580 --> 00:37:15.182 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you will bring glory to Jehovah

00:37:15.182 --> 00:37:17.184 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and not to yourselves.

